are in Juxian Alley.

284
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:00,020
The place we're going to eat at

285
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:01,780
is a diner that's about to open

286
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:03,860
in Juxian Alley.

287
00:16:04,140 --> 00:16:05,380
Before it officially opens,

288
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:07,620
they're offering

289
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,260
free tastings.

290
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:12,540
Free tastings?

291
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:14,580
Yes.

292
00:16:17,260 --> 00:16:18,380
Did you receive

293
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:19,980
that winning flyer?

294
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:21,660
You also know that?

295
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:24,300
I was actually worried

296
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,540
that I'm short on money,

297
00:16:25,540 --> 00:16:26,780
and inviting you to a meal

298
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:28,260
that's a free tasting

299
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:29,420
might upset you.

300
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:32,500
Judging by your expression,

301
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,940
could it be that you also
kept that flyer,

302
00:16:35,540 --> 00:16:37,940
thinking of going
for a free tasting someday?

303
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:40,620
That's perfect.

304
00:16:41,380 --> 00:16:43,500
Let's go for the free tasting right now.

305
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,580
It's almost curfew time.

306
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,180
The ancestor won't come.

307
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,040
Yangyang,

308
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:59,420
go to the kitchen and tell Grandpa
not to heat the dishes.

309
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,740
It's been reheated many times.

310
00:17:04,780 --> 00:17:06,420
Let's just eat already.

311
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:14,460
Auntie, cheer up.

312
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,620
Grandma always said

313
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:17,620
that sighing
would let fortune slip away.

314
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:21,020
There we go; the fortune is back.

315
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:26,820
Is this the place for the free tasting?

316
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:28,460
- Vice Prefect Lin.
- Vice Prefect Lin.

317
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:29,900
Please come in.

318
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:36,500
(Earth Room 1)
To Mr. Pei and Mr. Lin,

319
00:17:36,510 --> 00:17:37,420
let's drink.

320
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:38,420
Come on, come on.

321
00:17:38,420 --> 00:17:39,420
Cheers.

322
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:40,500
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

323
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,060
- We'll drink first.
- Cheers.

324
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,540
Mr. Lin, why didn't you drink?

325
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:52,980
This is kinda inappropriate, right?

326
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:54,020
Mr. Lin,

327
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:55,780
it was indeed wrong of us

328
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:57,300
to inflate the prices before.

329
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,220
Drink this cup,

330
00:17:58,220 --> 00:17:59,940
and don't hold it
against us anymore, okay?

331
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:00,820
Yes.

332
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:01,860
Sorry.

333
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:03,140
I don't drink alcohol.

334
00:18:03,780 --> 00:18:06,460
- Let me tell you something.
- Auntie,

335
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:07,780
what does he mean?

336
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:08,960
He doesn't drink alcohol.

337
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,400
People in this era like to say that.
It's more pretentious.

338
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:12,820
What is this?

339
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,860
You're being boring.

340
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:16,740
This is called lobster.

341
00:18:16,980 --> 00:18:19,260
It's the highest honor
we offer to our guests.

342
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:20,660
- Try it.
- But

343
00:18:20,660 --> 00:18:22,260
since we can't get the ingredient,

344
00:18:22,260 --> 00:18:24,780
we can only use steamed buns
as a substitute.

345
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:26,620
How about it?

346
00:18:26,620 --> 00:18:27,820
Give it a try.

347
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:29,380
Yes, try it.

348
00:18:29,380 --> 00:18:30,900
Please try it.

349
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:31,980
- Lobster?
- Here.

350
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:32,820
Yes.

351
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:35,260
- Vice Prefect, try it.
- Try it.

352
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:36,220
Delicious.

353
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:38,300
You're not eating or drinking.

354
00:18:38,530 --> 00:18:39,380
That's not okay.

355
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:40,780
You have to drink.

356
00:18:40,860 --> 00:18:41,700
Yes.

357
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:42,620
I don't drink alcohol.

358
00:18:42,860 --> 00:18:44,260
We can't drink anymore.

359
00:18:44,420 --> 00:18:45,940
Curfew is coming soon.

360
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:47,740
We can't leave the living area
during curfew.

361
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:50,460
I have to go back before curfew.

362
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:53,300
There's even less to worry about.

363
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:55,180
Just stay here and drink.

364
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:56,020
If you're drunk,

365
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:57,640
- stay here.
- Yes.

366
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,620
We can make room, right?

367
00:18:58,620 --> 00:19:00,460
Just stay here for the night.

368
00:19:00,580 --> 00:19:01,420
Vice Prefect,

369
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:04,380
you have to drink for my sake.

370
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:06,940
There's no official
who doesn't drink, right?

371
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,580
- Yes.
- If you don't drink this wine,

372
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:09,500
that means

373
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:10,860
you haven't forgiven us, right?

374
00:19:10,860 --> 00:19:11,800
You haven't forgiven us.

375
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:14,740
I didn't mean it that way.

376
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:17,180
Then just drink this.

377
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,380
- Just one cup.
- Just one cup.

378
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:22,000
It seems you are determined

379
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:23,620
to persuade me to drink this cup.

380
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:24,900
That's not true.

381
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:25,900
I'll drink first.

382
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:30,220
Look, she's drinking.

383
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:37,140
Good, good.

384
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:38,060
You can indeed drink.

385
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:39,360
We'll join you.

386
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,500
- We'll join you.
- Come on.

387
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,220
- Mr. Pei, join us.
- I'll have some soup.

388
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:43,700
Vice Prefect, let me tell you.

389
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:45,340
Where there's a first, there's a second.

390
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:46,540
Let's drink again.

391
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:47,940
I can't hold my drink.

392
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:49,460
You can.

393
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:50,940
Then I shall drink with you.

394
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,660
Great, come on.

395
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,220
Come on.

396
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,460
Vice Prefect Lin?

397
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:16,300
Vice Prefect?

398
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:18,340
- Vice Prefect Lin?
- Vice Prefect?

399
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:20,100
Finally touched the real person.

400
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:21,580
What are you doing?

401
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:23,180
This is our ancestor.

402
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,100
Jicai and I have already found out.

403
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:29,880
In the backyard of Yunshui Manor,

404
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,060
there's a gap when the guards
change shifts at night.

405
00:20:32,060 --> 00:20:33,460
If we can find the key

406
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:34,860
and avoid the curfew patrol,

407
00:20:34,860 --> 00:20:35,740
we'll have a chance

408
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,940
and sneak in before he sobers up.

409
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:40,780
Hurry up, or he'll sober up.

410
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:42,180
- Hurry up.
- Come on.

411
00:20:42,660 --> 00:20:43,500
Be quiet.

412
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,380
Slow down.

413
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:54,980
It's okay; keep going.

414
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:09,780
I can't find the key.

415
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:11,340
We can't find it.

416
00:21:11,540 --> 00:21:12,740
Can you two do this?

417
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:14,340
Let me do it.

418
00:21:14,340 --> 00:21:15,460
- Jicai.
- You do it.

419
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:30,380
(In this era,)

420
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:32,540
(does the master even carry keys?)

421
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:35,060
(Should we get
his attendant drunk instead?)

422
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,920
(Maybe it's hidden inside his clothes?)

423
00:21:43,820 --> 00:21:45,420
What are you going to do to me?

424
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:48,940
Stop!

425
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:58,980
This isn't really happening, is it?

426
00:21:58,980 --> 00:21:59,820
Grandma.

427
00:22:03,860 --> 00:22:05,420
(Our ancestor didn't pick)

428
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,580
(those things to target us, did he?)

429
00:22:08,540 --> 00:22:09,380
(Yes, yes.)

430
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,860
(He can't mean to hurt us, can he?)

431
00:22:11,860 --> 00:22:12,860
(Grandpa said)

432
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:14,660
(that before Lin Yan married)

433
00:22:14,660 --> 00:22:15,780
(Lady Shen,)

434
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:17,420
(he used to be quite ruthless.)

435
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:26,100
Gongcai, wake up.

436
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,660
- What's wrong with you?
- Dad.

437
00:22:28,340 --> 00:22:29,500
So easily frightened.

438
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:31,540
Then let's start with him.

439
00:22:31,540 --> 00:22:32,380
Yes.

440
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:33,500
Gongcai, Gongcai.

441
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:34,780
No, Dad.

442
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,380
Wake up, Dad!

443
00:22:36,380 --> 00:22:37,940
- Don't touch him.
- Dad.

444
00:22:38,780 --> 00:22:40,180
After all this trouble,

445
00:22:40,980 --> 00:22:42,300
you just wanted to get me drunk.

446
00:22:42,980 --> 00:22:43,820
How about this?

447
00:22:44,260 --> 00:22:45,360
I'll kill one of you first

448
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:46,660
to serve as a warning.

449
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:47,900
Then,

450
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,140
you'll be willing to reveal

451
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:52,180
your identities and purposes, right?

452
00:22:53,620 --> 00:22:54,540
No, no, no.

453
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,420
Don't, don't.

454
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:56,300
Ancestor, Ancestor.

455
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:57,980
Please, have mercy.

456
00:22:57,980 --> 00:22:59,820
Don't kill us,
especially not me, Ancestor.

457
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:00,960
Who said I'm your ancestor?

458
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:04,220
- Dad.
- I'm sorry. We're sorry.

459
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:05,740
Please, I'm begging you.

460
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,960
- Let go of my aunt.
- What are you up to?

461
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:10,960
We're sorry, we're sorry.

462
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:11,740
Auntie.

463
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,380
Please spare my daughter.

464
00:23:13,380 --> 00:23:14,300
Please don't.

465
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:15,700
We aren't up to anything.

466
00:23:15,700 --> 00:23:17,260
- Vice Prefect.
- I'll count to three.

467
00:23:17,260 --> 00:23:18,330
- Vice Prefect.
- No, no.

468
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:19,380
- Three.
- No.

469
00:23:19,380 --> 00:23:20,420
We aren't up to anything.

470
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:21,820
Two.

471
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:24,940
Vice Prefect.

472
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:26,340
One.

473
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,100
Actually, you're my fiancé.

474
00:23:34,860 --> 00:23:36,260
(Jicai, are you crazy?)

475
00:23:36,620 --> 00:23:37,580
(This is our ancestor.)

476
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:40,100
(When your grandpa told you
about our ancestor,)

477
00:23:40,340 --> 00:23:43,220
(did he say he had a fiancée
before he married into our family?)

478
00:23:43,420 --> 00:23:45,100
(He didn't mention it,)

479
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:46,860
(but those romance novels my mom loves)

480
00:23:46,860 --> 00:23:47,820
(are always like this.)

481
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:49,180
(The ruthless tycoon)

482
00:23:49,180 --> 00:23:50,580
(always has a mysterious fiancée.)

483
00:23:50,580 --> 00:23:51,480
(It's a common plot.)

484
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,480
(I admit I'm taking a gamble.)

485
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,780
(Oh, no, it's all over.)

486
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,580
(Don't panic yet.)

487
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,220
(Judging by the ancestor's look,)

488
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:03,700
(did Jicai actually guess right?)

489
00:24:06,860 --> 00:24:07,700
You say

490
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:11,980
you're my fiancée?

491
00:24:13,140 --> 00:24:14,020
Do you have any proof?

492
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:18,540
I know your real identity.

493
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:20,580
Qingyang,

494
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:22,340
Cui Che.

495
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:33,100
Vice Prefect Lin,

496
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:34,860
originally named Cui Che,

497
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:37,140
was from Qingyang County.

498
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:38,940
When he was eight years old,

499
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:40,300
his father

500
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:42,460
committed a capital offense.

501
00:24:42,980 --> 00:24:45,620
The Cui family was exterminated.

502
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:47,060
Only he

503
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:49,780
was fortunate enough to be saved.

504
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:53,700
He changed his name,
registered elsewhere, and survived.

505
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:57,740
Go on.

506
00:25:00,260 --> 00:25:02,220
The Cui family was exterminated.

507
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:05,740
You changed your name
and registered elsewhere

508
00:25:05,780 --> 00:25:06,940
to be safe.

509
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:15,180
But the family I was engaged to

510
00:25:16,060 --> 00:25:17,340
didn't have the surname Shen.

511
00:25:17,980 --> 00:25:19,680
We were promised
in marriage before birth.

512
00:25:19,940 --> 00:25:21,340
When the tragedy happened,

513
00:25:21,860 --> 00:25:23,220
you were only eight years old.

514
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:26,260
It's not strange
that you forgot my family name.

515
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:29,580
Poor you,
losing your family at a young age.

516
00:25:30,460 --> 00:25:32,420
You can't remember many things, can you?

517
00:25:33,620 --> 00:25:35,740
But please, rest easy.

518
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:37,340
We in business

519
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:38,540
know what to do.

520
00:25:38,820 --> 00:25:41,300
Since I'm your fiancée,

521
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:42,820
we're practically relatives.

522
00:25:43,820 --> 00:25:46,260
Why? We're not married.

523
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:49,300
It doesn't matter.

524
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:51,780
Anyway,

525
00:25:52,340 --> 00:25:53,860
we won't breathe a word

526
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:55,100
about your secret to anyone.

527
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,380
Think about it.

528
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:58,480
We're related by marriage.

529
00:25:58,660 --> 00:25:59,540
If we harm you,

530
00:25:59,540 --> 00:26:01,140
we'd be implicated too, right?

531
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:05,020
Yes, yes.

532
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:37,100
When you interrogated us earlier,

533
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:38,740
we indeed hid something.

534
00:26:38,740 --> 00:26:40,340
Please let us stay

535
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:42,900
in Yunshui Manor.

536
00:26:46,220 --> 00:26:47,540
You want to use me

537
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:48,980
to live in Yunshui Manor?

538
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:52,220
You could have just asked.

539
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:53,700
Why go through all this trouble?

540
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:55,740
So, you mean...

541
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:57,260
Absolutely impossible.

542
00:26:59,580 --> 00:27:01,500
I've actually thought of this answer.

543
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:03,260
A dignified Vice Prefect,

544
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:04,900
who eats a free meal at others' expense,

545
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:06,900
yet doesn't allow others
to do the same to him.

546
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:08,500
In that case,

547
00:27:09,020 --> 00:27:10,460
to have a place to stay,

548
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:12,300
I have to use unconventional methods.

549
00:27:12,940 --> 00:27:14,420
Mr. Pei, Mr. Pei.

550
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:15,780
Please get up and help me.

551
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:17,700
- Vice Prefect Lin abandoned me.
- Nonsense.

552
00:27:17,820 --> 00:27:19,760
Mr. Pei, speak up for me.

553
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:21,220
- Mr. Lin got promoted...
- Shut up.

554
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,660
He abandoned his wife.

555
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:28,100
Young Master.

556
00:27:32,460 --> 00:27:33,380
Do you want to die?

557
00:27:34,380 --> 00:27:35,780
You touched my mouth.

